Lemon Air Fryer Pound Cake 

3/4 cups all purpose flour
1/2 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 cup butter, softened
1 cup sugar
1 cup powdered sugar
4 Tbsp lemon juice
2 eggs
2 tsp pure vanilla extract
1/4 cup lemon juice

Preheat Air Fryer to 330 degrees F. Grease and flour a 6 cup bundt pan. https://tinyurl.com/y9us6ref

In a bowl, add the flour, baking powder, and salt together. 

In a separate bowl, add cream the butter, 1 cup of the sugar and mix well with a hand mixer. Keep mixer running at a low speed, add one egg at a time then vanilla.

Alternating and mixing after each addition, add the dry mixture to the butter mixture 1/4 cup of the lemon juice. Mix until just smooth.

Pour into the pan. And bake until the center has raised and when a toothpick is inserted into the center it comes out dry (about 30 to 45 minutes).

Meanwhile, make the glaze: In a small bowl, stir together the powdered sugar and 4 tbs lemon juice, 2 Tbsp at a time whisking between adding lemon juice. Allow to cool about pan 15 minutes and turn the cake out onto a plate. Drizzle on glaze with a spoon and slice and serve

Makes: 8 servings

